news.title: Lapsed building projects haunt Mumbai homebuyers
news.para: Especially since the city has innumerable tragic stories of families who paid tens of lakhs or even crores to book flats but have been unable to take possession of their homes for years.

news.title: Mumbai: Encroachers lay siege to high-rise in Lower Parel
news.para: The street in question is the same one where the BMC had implemented its ‘green mile’ project, a plan to develop a one-kilometre stretch into an ideal street for the civic ward and set a benchmark for street design.

news.title: Bengaluru: HC to hear plea of mortgagors of Aishwarya Apartments on March 7
news.para: The building was in the news recently after Canara Bank, through a court commissioner appointed by a city magistrate court, took physical possession of the building for a while on Thursday.

news.title: Pune: PMRDA's draft development plan in last stage of submission to government
news.para: "The committee conducting the hearings is expected to submit the report in the next 10 days," said PMRDA commissioner Rahul Mahiwal. The committee heard nearly 69,000 complaints.

news.title: Trichy corporation locks, seals shops to collect revenue
news.para: To push traders to pay their outstanding dues, the corporation has locked and sealed 55 shops and warned 20 others at Chathiram bus stand complex to pay their dues or face similar action.

news.title: Buoyant real estate may generate bumper revenue in Madhya Pradesh
news.para: “For 2022-23, Indore stamp and registrar department has a target of generating a total income of Rs 2,323 crore and of this, about Rs 1,800 crore of revenue has been generated through registration of around 1.4 lakh properties by starting of the March,” said DIG at Indore-Ujjain division stamp and registrar department Balkrishna More.

news.title: Indore development body to put 1,800 flats up for sale
news.para: The price of these property will range from Rs 10 lakh to Rs 40 lakh/unit and thus, the same is expected to attract the buyers of the middle-income group the most

news.title: Nagpur: MADC nets in Rs 43 crore through land lease to build upscale homes
news.para: Apart from the Mihan-SEZ, the MADC is also developing a domestic tariff area (DTA) close by which also has residential complexes. Mihan already has three major residential complexes in the DTA.

news.title: Kolkata development body to auction 11 small plots on freehold basis
news.para: Officials said the last time small plots in and around Kasba and Rajdanga were allotted through lottery was in 2009-2010, when it was given on leasehold basis.

news.title: China to guard against risks among property developers: Premier Li Keqiang
news.para: Premier Li Keqiang made guarding against risks to top property developers one of the government's priorities this year, amid still cautious buyer sentiment, following through on the work done at a key economic meeting in December.

news.title: UK property portal Rightmove sees fewer house hunters as market slows
news.para: Shares in the company, which runs the UK's largest property website, slipped as much as 3.7% to a seven-week low of 540 pence in morning trade and the stock was the top percentage loser on the blue-chip FTSE 100 index.

news.title: Blackstone defaults on Nordic mortgage-backed bond
news.para: The private equity firm sought an extension from the bondholders to repay the debt, but they voted against it, a source familiar with the matter told Reuters.

news.title: Amazon delays construction of second phase of Virginia headquarters
news.para: John Schoettler, Amazon's real estate chief, said in a statement on Friday the company was pushing out the date for groundbreaking of PenPlace, the second phase of the northern Virginia campus.

news.title: DDA lodges complaint with CBI over 'lapses' in Signature View Apartments construction
news.para: The DDA also conducted a vigilance inquiry, following the Lt Governor's directions, to ascertain the role of officials in the case.

news.title: Maharashtra realty agent held for cheating
news.para: Vijay Kumar and his aide Sridhar from Sheikpet approached Ravi to buy four plots in the city through one Santhosh Kumar. Ravi convinced the duo that land owner, Naga Kishore, and two others wanted to sell four plots.
